name: The eleventh incarnation. The mantis.
description:
Hatching was quick and painless. Having adjusted the focus, I saw my mother. But, the joy of birth was quickly replaced by fear. Mom chewed my brother, who was born a little earlier. I ran away and never returned to the place of birth. 

Life flowed incredibly slowly and monotonously. The mind was clouded and cleared only when the victim appeared in the field of vision. Instant mobilization of the whole organism brought not only the body, but also the nervous system into a state of combat readiness. Instantly, I remembered my whole life and all my previous thoughts. A series of flashbacks covered me and held me until the victim came within striking distance. Hit. Absorption of food. Sleep.

One day I woke up in His warm arms. He took me to a big cave with trees. He fed me and talked to me. 
I also met a female there, whom I impregnated. I died right after mating. She chewed off my head.
